name: Logbook - Im out
description:
2022/02/22

“The first moments out of the atmosphere are the most harrowing, as your ear has been abruptly torn from the comfort there was on earth, and now you are placed in the void of space – what you hear is the resounding of beings far away. 

This change brings a resignification to all fundamental sounds that we know, mainly due to the fact that our sound frequency range is quite limited (we expanded the sound range from 1 hz to 100 khz, to capture the most diverse oscillations of space, transforming them to our hearing range).

This is the beginning of an intergalactic search for artifacts, records, impressions and interactions with key resonances echoing across the vast infinity of stars.” 

Each logbook will have an audiotrack, an oscillator gif and a brief description of the encounter.
GIF - 720x720p
MP3 - 320kbps
